  "signature": "ed25519:b7e2f4a1c9d305e8f6b2a4c7e1d903f5a8c2b6e4d1f709a3c5b8e2f4a1c9d305",
  "hasCredibilityFactor": [
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Software quality assurance",
      "factorStandard": "NASA-STD-7009B",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/sqa-openfast-level3",
      "rationale": "OpenFAST v3.4.0 is maintained under a formal version-controlled repository (NREL GitHub) with CI/CD pipelines executing regression tests on every pull request. The codebase carries a DOE-funded software quality plan conforming to NQA-1 Subpart 2.7 requirements. All aeroelastic modules used in this COU (AeroDyn v15, ElastoDyn, ServoDyn) passed the NREL regression test suite with zero failures at the pinned commit hash used for production runs. Level 3 is required because simulation outputs directly inform certification margin calculations reviewed by a DNV-accredited body."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "NASA-STD-7009B",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/code-verification-level3",
      "rationale": "Code-to-code verification was performed against HAWC2 v12.9 for the IEA 15-MW reference turbine under steady uniform inflow and turbulent DLC 1.1 seeds. Flapwise DEL agreement was within 4.2% RMS across all mean wind speed bins 4–24 m/s. Edgewise DEL agreement was within 2.8% RMS. These bounds are consistent with published OC5 and OC6 phase benchmarks and satisfy the Level 3 threshold established in the project verification plan."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "NASA-STD-7009B",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/discretization-error-level2",
      "rationale": "A time-step convergence study was conducted at dt = 0.0125 s, 0.025 s, and 0.05 s for representative 10-minute DLC 1.1 seeds at 8, 12, and 16 m/s mean wind speeds. Richardson extrapolation yielded an estimated discretization error of 0.9% in blade root flapwise DEL at the production dt = 0.025 s. The aerodynamic blade element discretization was assessed using 20, 30, and 50 stations; DEL sensitivity was below 0.5% above 30 stations, and the production model uses 40 stations. Level 2 is required given the moderate consequence class of the laminate sizing decision."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "NASA-STD-7009B",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/solver-error-level2",
      "rationale": "OpenFAST uses a modular implicit-explicit coupling scheme. Solver residuals were monitored for all 600 DLC 1.1 seeds; maximum coupling iteration residual remained below 1e-5 in all cases. No non-convergence events were recorded. The fixed-point iteration tolerance of 1e-6 is consistent with the Level 2 requirement documented in the project numerical methods plan."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "NASA-STD-7009B",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/use-error-level3",
      "rationale": "All simulation input decks were peer-reviewed by a second qualified analyst prior to production runs. A documented pre-run checklist covering turbine geometry, controller parameters, wind file paths, and output channel selection was completed and signed off. Post-run sanity checks (rotor speed, pitch activity, power curve) were compared against manufacturer data and confirmed plausible. No anomalous runs were identified in the 600-seed ensemble."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "NASA-STD-7009B",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Model form credibility for aeroelastic DEL prediction is the most consequential factor in this COU and warrants the most detailed treatment. The IEA 15-MW is a conceptual reference turbine without an operational prototype, which limits direct model-form validation to subscale and analogous-turbine evidence. OpenFAST employs Blade Element Momentum (BEM) theory with Prandtl tip-loss, dynamic stall (DBEM with Beddoes-Leishman), and tower shadow corrections. These physics representations are well-established for megawatt-class turbines operating in attached-flow regimes typical of DLC 1.1 below rated wind speed. Published literature (Jonkman et al. 2009, Madsen et al. 2020) demonstrates that BEM-based aeroelastic codes predict flapwise fatigue loads within 5–10% of field measurements on comparable turbines (NREL 5-MW, DTU 10-MW). The achieved Level 3 reflects the absence of full-scale IEA 15-MW field data and reliance on analogous-turbine evidence chains. The required Level 4 is set because blade root laminate sizing directly enters the certification safety case. This gap is acknowledged as the primary credibility shortfall and is mitigated by applying a 10% DEL load amplification factor in the laminate sizing calculations, consistent with IEC 61400-1 Ed. 4 partial safety factor guidance for simulation-only load bases. The assessment team reviewed the gap against DNV-ST-0376 Section 7.3 guidance on model uncertainty treatment and concluded the amplification factor constitutes an adequate engineering compensating measure for the current design phase. A follow-on measurement campaign on the first prototype unit is planned to close this gap prior to type certification.",
      "achievedLevelJustification": "Level 3 achieved based on analogous-turbine validation evidence and published BEM accuracy benchmarks; Level 4 not achievable without IEA 15-MW prototype field data."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "NASA-STD-7009B",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-inputs-level3",
      "rationale": "Blade structural properties (stiffness, mass distribution) were derived from the IEA 15-MW public reference dataset v1.1. Aerodynamic polars were generated with XFOIL and corrected for 3D rotational augmentation using the Snel correction. Wind turbulence inputs used TurbSim v2.0 with IEC Kaimal spectral model, Class IB turbulence intensity, and 600 s seeds. Soil-foundation stiffness was set to rigid per the land-based variant definition. All input sources are documented in the model input log (MIL-2024-IEA15-v3) with version hashes."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "NASA-STD-7009B",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-samples-level2",
      "rationale": "The 2024 strain gauge campaign instrumented two blades on an analogous 13-MW turbine of similar chord and thickness distribution. Thirty 10-minute records were acquired spanning wind speeds 6–18 m/s under near-neutral atmospheric stability. The sample set is sufficient to characterize mean DEL trends across the operational envelope relevant to DLC 1.1, satisfying Level 2 requirements."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "NASA-STD-7009B",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-conditions-level2",
      "rationale": "Meteorological mast measurements confirmed IEC Class IB turbulence conditions during the campaign period. Atmospheric stability was characterized via Obukhov length; records with |L| < 200 m (strongly stable or convective) were excluded, leaving 28 usable records in near-neutral conditions matching the TurbSim Kaimal model assumptions. Sensor calibration certificates were current at the time of measurement."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "NASA-STD-7009B",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/input-equivalency-level2",
      "rationale": "Simulation input parameters for the validation runs were matched to measured site conditions: hub-height mean wind speed, turbulence intensity, wind shear exponent (alpha = 0.18 ± 0.03), and air density (1.225 kg/m³ adjusted for site elevation). Rotor speed and pitch angle were set to match the analogous turbine controller response recorded during the campaign. Parameter matching is documented in the validation input equivalency matrix (VIEM-2024-v2)."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "NASA-STD-7009B",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/output-comparison-level3",
      "rationale": "Simulated blade root flapwise DEL (1 Hz equivalent, m=10 Wöhler slope) was compared against strain-gauge-derived DEL for 28 matched records. Mean absolute percentage error was 6.3%; bias was +2.1% (simulation over-predicts). Edgewise DEL MAPE was 4.7%. Comparison plots and statistical summary are documented in validation report VR-2024-IEA15-DEL. The over-prediction bias is conservative for laminate sizing purposes."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "NASA-STD-7009B",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/qoi-relevance-level3",
      "rationale": "The quantities of interest in the validation activity (blade root flapwise and edgewise bending moment DELs at 1 Hz equivalent with Wöhler exponent m=10) are identical to those used in the certification laminate sizing calculations. No transformation or extrapolation of QOI is required between the validation evidence and the COU application."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "NASA-STD-7009B",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/validation-relevance-level3",
      "rationale": "Validation was performed on an analogous 13-MW turbine rather than the IEA 15-MW reference turbine itself, introducing a relevance gap. The analogous turbine shares similar non-dimensional blade geometry (solidity, twist distribution, relative thickness) and operates in the same wind class. Scale effects on DEL are expected to be secondary relative to turbulence loading, which is matched. Level 2 is achieved; Level 3 would require validation on the target turbine class or a certified scaling methodology, neither of which is available at this design phase."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/wind-turbine-del-cou1-decision-20260419",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/iea-wind-task37-lead-assessor",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment for the OpenFAST DLC 1.1 DEL prediction COU is accepted with conditions. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed their required levels. The model form factor achieves Level 3 against a required Level 4; this gap is mitigated by a documented 10% DEL amplification factor applied in laminate sizing, consistent with IEC 61400-1 Ed. 4 partial safety factor guidance. The validation relevance factor achieves Level 2 against a required Level 3 due to the absence of IEA 15-MW prototype data; this is accepted for the current preliminary design phase with a mandatory follow-on measurement campaign condition prior to type certification. The overall credibility profile is sufficient to support blade root laminate sizing decisions at the current design gate.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
